variable: It's a name given to a memory location where we stored a value

Datatypes: 1. Primary Datatype --> Int, float, char, void, double
                  i) Integer Datatype: whole numbers value (ex. 1,2 5,12 )
                  ii) Float: fraction numbers  (ex. 20.5,45.285 ) 
                  iii) character: One char only ( ex. 9, s, d )
                  iv) double: used for store big number

                  
                  
           2. Derived Datatype --> array, structure, union, pointers
           3. user defined ------> typedef, enumeration
            

